rComments: He is the equivalent of Shane from Love is Blind.
grading is completely arbitrary. be on his good side and you'll get a good grade.

The course material is pretty boring but he really ties in a lot of stories from his experience and current/past events to the material which makes it a lot more interesting. Great prof, very inspiring - i'd say the best experience I had with a prof at Uottawa for sure.

Professor Segals lectures are not helpful at all since he reads off the slides and goes on random tangents. He always seems distracted in class and is rude to students. He says hell post the lecture recordings, but do not trust this since he probably wont. His grading is arbitrary which makes it difficult to get a high grade. Avoid if possible.
